{"TopicId":203223,"ForumId":70,"TopicTitle":"Increase realism, not with rescale, but by tweaking engines perf with MM patches, but how ?","CreatedByName":"kurgut","CreatedById":188918,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-06-23T17:27:37Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"kurgut","CreatedById":188918,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-06-23T17:27:37Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHi, as the title suggests, I\u0027d like to keep stock system as is, but patching all engines to decrease their performance, and thus allow more IRL-like rockets stages (ei. with more than 1 stage to orbit...). On what should I focus for that, increasing all engines masses for instance?\u003Cbr\u003E\nIf you have some idea about it, and also know some hint about how to achieve that with \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Module Manager (mod)\u0022\u003EMM\u003C/abbr\u003E patches, help would be grealty apreciated !\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nThanks ! \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nKurg\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Cavscout74","CreatedById":181783,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-06-23T18:24:16Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLowering Isp would work as well.\u00A0 There was a tech tree mod that had an optional patch that did that, but I can\u0027t remember which one.\u00A0\u00A0 \u003Cs\u003E(Give me a minute....)\u003C/s\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/188918-kurgut/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022188918\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/188918-kurgut/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@kurgut\u003C/a\u003E Found it:\u00A0 Simplex Tech Tree.\u00A0 Apparently it modifies only the in-atmosphere Isp \u0026amp; thrust curve, leaving vacuum stats untouched.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedauthorid=\u0022122369\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed6709933569\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/174731-111x-tetrix-techtree-282-and-simplex-techtree-1181/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022 style=\u0022height:197px;max-width:502px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222021-06-23T18:39:12Z\u0022 title=\u002206/23/2021 06:39  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00223 yr\u0022\u003EJune 23, 2021\u003C/time\u003E by Cavscout74\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"theJesuit","CreatedById":122369,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-06-23T19:19:17Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223993579\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022203223\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221624469257\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022188918\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022kurgut\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, kurgut said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHi, as the title suggests, I\u0027d like to keep stock system as is, but patching all engines to decrease their performance, and thus allow more IRL-like rockets stages (ei. with more than 1 stage to orbit...). On what should I focus for that, increasing all engines masses for instance?\u003Cbr\u003E\nIf you have some idea about it, and also know some hint about how to achieve that with \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Module Manager (mod)\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Module Manager (mod)\u0022\u003EMM\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E patches, help would be grealty apreciated !\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223993611\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022203223\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221624472656\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022181783\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Cavscout74\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n38 minutes ago, Cavscout74 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLowering Isp would work as well.\u00A0 There was a tech tree mod that had an optional patch that did that, but I can\u0027t remember which one.\u00A0\u00A0 \u003Cs\u003E(Give me a minute....)\u003C/s\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/188918-kurgut/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022188918\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/188918-kurgut/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@kurgut\u003C/a\u003E Found it:\u00A0 Simplex Tech Tree.\u00A0 Apparently it modifies only the in-atmosphere Isp \u0026amp; thrust curve, leaving vacuum stats untouched.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedauthorid=\u0022122369\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed7439059315\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/174731-111x-tetrix-techtree-282-and-simplex-techtree-1181/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022 style=\u0022height:195px;max-width:502px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHi!\u00A0 Yes, you can even just take the specific \u003Cstrong\u003E.cfg \u003C/strong\u003Efile out of the zip and place it anywhere in your gamedata folder.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlternatively, make your own cfg using the following:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cpre class=\u0022ipsCode prettyprint lang-html prettyprinted\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003E@PART[*]:HAS[@MODULE[ModuleEngines*]]::Final\n\u00A0\u00A0 \u00A0{\u00A0\u00A0 \u00A0@MODULE[ModuleEngines*]\n\u00A0\u00A0 \u00A0\u00A0\u00A0 \u00A0\u00A0\u00A0 \u00A0{ \u00A0\u00A0 \u00A0@atmosphereCurve\n\u00A0\u00A0 \u00A0\u00A0\u00A0 \u00A0\u00A0\u00A0 \u00A0\u00A0\u00A0 \u00A0\u00A0\u00A0 \u00A0{\u00A0\u00A0 \u00A0@key[1, ] *= 1\n\u00A0\u00A0 \u00A0\u00A0\u00A0 \u00A0\u00A0\u00A0 \u00A0\u00A0\u00A0 \u00A0\u00A0\u00A0 \u00A0\u00A0\u00A0 \u00A0@key,1[1, ] *= .7\n\u00A0\u00A0 \u00A0\u00A0\u00A0 \u00A0\u00A0\u00A0 \u00A0\u00A0\u00A0 \u00A0\u00A0\u00A0 \u00A0\u00A0\u00A0 \u00A0@key,2[1, ] *= .35\n\u00A0\u00A0 \u00A0\u00A0\u00A0 \u00A0\u00A0\u00A0 \u00A0\u00A0\u00A0 \u00A0\u00A0\u00A0 \u00A0}\n\u00A0\u00A0 \u00A0\u00A0\u00A0 \u00A0\u00A0\u00A0 \u00A0}\n\u00A0\u00A0 \u00A0}\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/pre\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt really makes you need two stages to get you out of the atmosphere.\u00A0 By the time you hit say 20kms, the atmosphere cure is pretty much close to the vacuum, but your first stage engines have only had 70% efficiency and thrust to get you there, and for most stock engines and tank mass that means it is much better to drop them.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhere I got this idea from, and all credit should go to here:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedauthorid=\u0022152759\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed4800646433\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/169534-simple-rss-patch-all-ksp-versions/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022 style=\u0022height:195px;max-width:502px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe difference with the SSRSS patch is that it changes all the keys to .7, meaning vacuum engines are also made less goodly too.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOn a side note, can I recommend as well, SIMPLEXResources?\u00A0 If you are into \u003Cabbr title=\u0022In-Situ Resource Utilization\u0022\u003EISRU\u003C/abbr\u003E for your bases et al, this gives a slightly more complex feel.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis mod changes both the tank ratios and engine requirements from 1.1:0.9\u00A0\u003Cspan\u003EOx:\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Liquid Fuel\u0022\u003ELF\u003C/abbr\u003E to 3:1 which is more \u0027real\u0027, but doesn\u0027t change the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Specific Impulse (rocketry) or Internet Service Provider\u0022\u003EISP\u003C/abbr\u003E or thrust.\u00A0 The main bonus for this is that you have three (or four) different ores to mine for.\u00A0 You need NaturalOre, which is plentiful to produce Oxidizer.\u00A0 And HydrateOre (or Saturate) to produce LiquidFuel.\u00A0 HydrateOre is harder to come by, like polar regions on the Mun.\u00A0 It is plentiful on Minmus, but Minmus has no NaturalOre.\u00A0 Given that most rocket fuel mass is oxidizer (I think in real life?) This means that you could mine for only one resource and take the fuel with you.\u00A0 Kind-a-like suggestions for real life missions, taking hydrogen with us to produce rocket fuel elsewhere.\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kurgut","CreatedById":188918,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-06-26T05:02:00Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/181783-cavscout74/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022181783\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/181783-cavscout74/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Cavscout74\u003C/a\u003E and \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/122369-thejesuit/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022122369\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/122369-thejesuit/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@theJesuit\u003C/a\u003E thanks both for your answers, that\u0027s exactly what I needed !\u003Cbr\u003E\nAnd yes, TheJesuit, SimplexRessources would be good by even increasing the fuel mass the a more IRL-like model (RP1/lox is something like 1/2.5 IIRC). For the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022In-Situ Resource Utilization\u0022\u003EISRU\u003C/abbr\u003E stuff I uses Kerbalism anyway, but I take note of it.\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nThanks again \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"theJesuit","CreatedById":122369,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-06-26T07:10:26Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223995408\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022203223\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221624683720\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022188918\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022kurgut\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, kurgut said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/181783-cavscout74/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022181783\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/181783-cavscout74/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Cavscout74\u003C/a\u003E and \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/122369-thejesuit/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022122369\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/122369-thejesuit/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@theJesuit\u003C/a\u003E thanks both for your answers, that\u0027s exactly what I needed !\u003Cbr\u003E\nAnd yes, TheJesuit, SimplexRessources would be good by even increasing the fuel mass the a more IRL-like model (RP1/lox is something like 1/2.5 IIRC). For the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022In-Situ Resource Utilization\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022In-Situ Resource Utilization\u0022\u003EISRU\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E stuff I uses Kerbalism anyway, but I take note of it.\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nThanks again \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou\u0027re welcome.\u00A0 The ratio was suggested by\u00A0riocrokite in his mod SAFIRE.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedauthorid=\u0022129319\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed1389154942\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/181591-16x-safire-stockalike-adjustments-to-fuels-isru-ratios-and-engines-21-01-2019/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022 style=\u0022height:196px;max-width:502px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo it was a basic rounding concept. It turns out in my latest musing in extending Simplex Resources to support cryo engines that there is a lovely symmetry from 3:1 to 1:3.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso,\u00A0 with Kerbalism Simplex the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022In-Situ Resource Utilization\u0022\u003EISRU\u003C/abbr\u003E is much more stockalike.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Cavscout74","CreatedById":181783,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-06-26T20:33:37Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223995408\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022203223\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221624683720\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022188918\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022kurgut\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n15 hours ago, kurgut said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/181783-cavscout74/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022181783\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/181783-cavscout74/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Cavscout74\u003C/a\u003E and \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/122369-thejesuit/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022122369\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/122369-thejesuit/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@theJesuit\u003C/a\u003E thanks both for your answers, that\u0027s exactly what I needed !\u003Cbr\u003E\nAnd yes, TheJesuit, SimplexRessources would be good by even increasing the fuel mass the a more IRL-like model (RP1/lox is something like 1/2.5 IIRC). For the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022In-Situ Resource Utilization\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022In-Situ Resource Utilization\u0022\u003EISRU\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E stuff I uses Kerbalism anyway, but I take note of it.\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nThanks again \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nGlad I could help\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Jimbodiah","CreatedById":152759,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-06-27T14:51:02Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSSRSS was really awesome:\u00A0do the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Real Solar System (mod)\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Real Solar System (mod)\u0022\u003ERSS\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E bit but not take ages to get anywhere. Also really detailed surfaces due to using the same textures on 1/10 the size spheres \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nToo bad it was abandoned and never picked up by anyone.\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nI wish KSP had a setting to use kerbol or a 1/10 \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Real Solar System (mod)\u0022\u003Erss\u003C/abbr\u003E version out of the box.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222021-06-27T14:51:54Z\u0022 title=\u002206/27/2021 02:51  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00223 yr\u0022\u003EJune 27, 2021\u003C/time\u003E by Jimbodiah\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"}]}